          | Topic Focus – SSH Components and Key Roles  
          |  
          | SSH Architecture:  
          |     - Client: Initiates the connection  
          |     - Server: Accepts and manages incoming SSH requests  
          |     - Session: Encrypted communication channel between client and server  

          | Key Types:  
          |     - User Key  
          |         → Asymmetric public key used to authenticate user to server  
          |     - Host Key  
          |         → Asymmetric public key used to verify server identity to client  
          |     - Session Key  
          |         → Symmetric key generated during handshake to encrypt session traffic  

          | Configuration Files:  
          |     - Client Config: `/etc/ssh/ssh_config`  
          |         → Controls client-side SSH behavior  
          |     - Server Config: `/etc/ssh/sshd_config`  
          |         → Defines server-side SSH settings and access rules  
          |     - Known Hosts: `~/.ssh/known_hosts`  
          |         → Stores trusted server fingerprints for client verification  

